WEBVTT

00:02:08.194 --> 00:02:10.396
Since when were you...?

00:02:11.264 --> 00:02:12.799
Water sploosh.

00:02:14.300 --> 00:02:15.435
You know this?

00:02:15.902 --> 00:02:18.738
I think I know, I don't think I know.

00:02:19.172 --> 00:02:21.641
I don't think I know that I know.

00:02:21.708 --> 00:02:24.811
I think I know
even though I don't think I know.

00:02:27.280 --> 00:02:28.214
Which is it?!

00:02:30.650 --> 00:02:31.551
Hey!

00:03:02.248 --> 00:03:04.183
Hey, Spike, where the hell are we?!

00:03:04.717 --> 00:03:06.586
-Isn't it Earth?
-Earth?

00:03:07.387 --> 00:03:09.322
Hey, this ship was headed for Mars!

00:03:09.689 --> 00:03:11.758
Why the hell are we on Earth
all of a sudden?!

00:03:11.824 --> 00:03:14.761
-I don't know.
-Shit, this isn't funny.

00:03:15.261 --> 00:03:17.196
While we're wasting time, our fugitive...

00:03:17.730 --> 00:03:19.465
It was the first big one in a while.

00:03:20.266 --> 00:03:22.302
-In any case, why the hell are we on--?
-Jet.

00:03:23.636 --> 00:03:24.671
The women are gone.

00:03:30.577 --> 00:03:33.980
<i>Listen, if you lead me</i>
<i>to that "water sploosh" place,</i>

00:03:34.247 --> 00:03:35.515
<i>I'll give you something good.</i>

00:03:35.582 --> 00:03:36.950
<i>Good thing? What?</i>

00:03:37.450 --> 00:03:40.286
Something very tremendously
wonderfully good.

00:03:41.888 --> 00:03:46.392
Something very tremendously
wonderfully good!

00:04:23.396 --> 00:04:24.330
Hot!

00:04:25.331 --> 00:04:27.433
Hot! Hot! Hot!

00:04:40.613 --> 00:04:41.614
This!

00:04:43.283 --> 00:04:45.618
Water sploosh!

00:04:49.489 --> 00:04:52.792
I knew I shouldn't have trusted you.

00:04:58.765 --> 00:05:00.400
Hey, I found Ed!

00:05:01.534 --> 00:05:03.403
Ed has been found?

00:05:03.870 --> 00:05:05.004
What? You know them?

00:05:05.071 --> 00:05:07.874
...35 point 38 point 0, 35 point 48
point 1, 35 point 48 point 2...

00:05:07.940 --> 00:05:08.808
This!

00:05:08.875 --> 00:05:10.410
This! This! This!

00:05:10.877 --> 00:05:13.012
-Hey, can I have your nails?
-Nails?

00:05:13.079 --> 00:05:15.948
I'm collecting them! Can I, please?
Just the pinky will do!

00:05:16.015 --> 00:05:17.817
...35 point 52 point 3, 35 point...

00:05:17.884 --> 00:05:19.385
This! This!

00:05:19.452 --> 00:05:21.788
-Come on, can I have it? Please?
-What are you guys?!

00:05:21.854 --> 00:05:22.822
Hey!

00:05:32.832 --> 00:05:33.833
Ed?!

00:05:35.935 --> 00:05:38.638
Is that really you... Ed?

00:05:50.416 --> 00:05:52.385
I'm sorry about that.

00:05:52.852 --> 00:05:56.355
That's the best way
to make the kids listen.

00:05:57.056 --> 00:05:57.924
It's all right.

00:05:59.926 --> 00:06:02.395
Is Ed from this place?

00:06:02.862 --> 00:06:05.965
She wandered in about five years ago.

00:06:06.599 --> 00:06:10.136
Before I knew it, she was eating with us
as if it had always been that way.

00:06:10.903 --> 00:06:14.040
And about three years ago,
she wandered away...

00:06:14.674 --> 00:06:16.776
as if she was a cat or something.

00:06:17.677 --> 00:06:20.847
I was wondering
how she was doing nowadays.

00:06:21.681 --> 00:06:23.716
But I didn't think
she would suddenly appear.

00:06:24.951 --> 00:06:26.719
All right, it's time to eat!

00:06:34.393 --> 00:06:36.662
Dear Lord, up in the heaven.

00:06:36.729 --> 00:06:38.865
Never mind the rest. Let's eat!

00:06:39.499 --> 00:06:41.067
Let's eat!

00:06:48.775 --> 00:06:50.176
I have to get going now.

00:06:50.743 --> 00:06:52.578
What, you can stay longer, right?

00:06:52.812 --> 00:06:55.782
-I'm actually looking for something.
-Ed knows where it is.

00:06:56.482 --> 00:06:59.819
We just came here for food.

00:07:01.187 --> 00:07:02.421
You...

00:07:02.955 --> 00:07:05.424
You have to give me something good!

00:07:06.159 --> 00:07:07.026
Oh, yeah, Ed.

00:07:07.894 --> 00:07:11.097
There's something good
in the desk drawer over there.

00:07:11.164 --> 00:07:13.533
-Something good?
-Go get it.

00:07:13.966 --> 00:07:15.735
Something good!

00:07:15.802 --> 00:07:17.570
Inside that drawer.

00:07:21.908 --> 00:07:23.109
Not that.

00:07:24.777 --> 00:07:26.913
Yeah, that. Open it!

00:07:33.553 --> 00:07:34.687
Her father.

00:07:35.154 --> 00:07:36.055
Whose?

00:07:36.722 --> 00:07:40.493
He came looking for Ed
about two months ago.

00:07:40.560 --> 00:07:43.596
He said he forgot
that he had put her in an orphanage,

00:07:43.996 --> 00:07:48.468
and that he had been looking for 7 years,
hopping around the world.

00:07:49.969 --> 00:07:51.838
I hope she will be able to meet him.

00:07:52.104 --> 00:07:55.208
People have to cherish
what ties they have.

00:08:09.555 --> 00:08:10.223
Yeah!

00:08:27.173 --> 00:08:29.141
Are you Faye?

00:08:31.577 --> 00:08:32.712
Impossible.

00:08:33.779 --> 00:08:34.780
Really?

00:08:35.214 --> 00:08:37.116
It's me, Sally Yung!

00:08:37.917 --> 00:08:39.886
I was in your high school
graduating class!

00:08:46.025 --> 00:08:47.226
Are you all right?

00:08:50.897 --> 00:08:52.265
I was really surprised.

00:08:52.832 --> 00:08:56.536
I thought you were a ghost.
You look just like you did back then.

00:08:57.003 --> 00:09:00.072
You know, they say ghosts appear
in places where they have regrets.

00:09:01.073 --> 00:09:02.909
Oh, yeah, I remember now.

00:09:02.975 --> 00:09:06.112
You were put in cold sleep
after that accident.

00:09:06.712 --> 00:09:08.915
-That's why you still look the same.
-Accident?

00:09:09.549 --> 00:09:12.318
Faye... you don't remember?

00:09:14.186 --> 00:09:15.254
I...

00:09:16.556 --> 00:09:18.558
Grandma!

00:09:23.062 --> 00:09:25.031
Grandma, we gotta go back now.

00:09:25.197 --> 00:09:26.699
Is it that time already?

00:09:31.804 --> 00:09:33.806
Do you know who this is?

00:09:35.608 --> 00:09:36.809
I bet you don't know.

00:09:37.109 --> 00:09:39.912
-Actually, she's--
-A ghost.

00:09:43.182 --> 00:09:44.617
Goodbye. Take care.

00:10:19.619 --> 00:10:22.888
Hey, you guys! What's with
the course change without asking?!

00:10:23.756 --> 00:10:26.058
Our plans have all been screwed
because of it!

00:10:26.125 --> 00:10:28.794
I don't appreciate
you doing things on your own!

00:10:45.211 --> 00:10:47.380
You want to smell something really good?

00:11:04.163 --> 00:11:06.132
What's with them?

00:11:06.799 --> 00:11:08.834
What are they being so secretive about?

00:11:08.901 --> 00:11:09.902
Leave them alone.

00:11:10.369 --> 00:11:12.371
Maybe they're too hungry
for their own good.

00:11:13.205 --> 00:11:16.675
Humans go insane if they don't eat food.

00:11:17.143 --> 00:11:18.144
Fifty million?

00:11:19.879 --> 00:11:21.414
I see. Pretty big.

00:11:22.114 --> 00:11:25.251
"Appledelhi Siniz Hesap Lutfen."

00:11:34.360 --> 00:11:36.762
Would you like one, Mackenroe?

00:11:36.929 --> 00:11:38.197
That's McIntire.

00:11:38.731 --> 00:11:40.800
No, thank you, Mr. Appledelhi.

00:11:41.067 --> 00:11:43.169
You sure? Eggs are good.

00:11:43.369 --> 00:11:48.174
As they say, power and charge.
That's what's important, Macintosh.

00:11:48.240 --> 00:11:49.875
That's McIntire.

00:11:50.009 --> 00:11:53.479
Why is it that you can't ever remember
your assistant's name?

00:11:55.181 --> 00:11:57.149
Don't worry
about the small things in life.

00:12:02.922 --> 00:12:05.257
-Hurry, Macky-Mike!
-That's McIntire!

00:13:32.945 --> 00:13:34.313
Watch where you're going!

00:13:39.251 --> 00:13:40.152
Hey.

00:13:40.853 --> 00:13:41.520
Sorry.

00:13:42.521 --> 00:13:43.489
Sorry?

00:13:45.858 --> 00:13:46.926
I...

00:13:53.032 --> 00:13:54.033
I have to go.

00:14:06.445 --> 00:14:09.481
Going out? Where are you going?

00:14:12.618 --> 00:14:15.054
I finally remembered where I belong.

00:14:15.554 --> 00:14:16.422
Where you belong?

00:14:17.089 --> 00:14:21.427
You have someone waiting for you, too.
You have somewhere you belong.

00:14:22.061 --> 00:14:23.429
You should go look for it, too.

00:14:25.931 --> 00:14:29.335
That's the best thing, you know.

00:14:40.246 --> 00:14:42.281
This one is a piece of cake.

00:14:42.615 --> 00:14:44.516
Fifty million is right there!

00:14:46.252 --> 00:14:48.988
If they can eat sukiyaki filled with meat,
then they--

00:14:49.054 --> 00:14:50.222
Faye went out.

00:14:50.589 --> 00:14:53.259
Again?
Where the hell did she go this time?

00:14:57.062 --> 00:15:00.332
"A woman's heart
and the skies of Ganymede," was it?

00:15:06.972 --> 00:15:08.307
You're Appledelhi?

00:15:10.242 --> 00:15:11.510
Can you come along with us?

00:15:12.011 --> 00:15:14.446
Cooperate with us
if you don't wanna get hurt.

00:15:15.180 --> 00:15:17.950
Who are you guys?
Don't interrupt our work!

00:15:18.017 --> 00:15:19.018
Work?

00:15:19.084 --> 00:15:23.455
What does this Earth need
to regain a peaceful peace?

00:15:23.522 --> 00:15:26.392
This Earth of wild chaos!
Is it the cosmos?

00:15:27.459 --> 00:15:30.029
That is a map! A map!

00:15:30.095 --> 00:15:33.165
Yes, happiness comes
in the form of a map!

00:15:33.232 --> 00:15:37.369
We are creating maps to save the Earth!

00:15:38.037 --> 00:15:39.705
A map?

00:15:39.972 --> 00:15:43.542
But meteors fall often
and change the landscape.

00:15:44.376 --> 00:15:49.181
That's why we're globetrotting.
We're chasing after every meteor.

00:15:49.248 --> 00:15:52.117
Until every single meteor falls to Earth!

00:15:55.487 --> 00:15:56.622
Enough with the excuses!

00:16:00.192 --> 00:16:01.226
You!

00:16:04.530 --> 00:16:06.365
I wasn't expecting someone this adept.

00:16:31.156 --> 00:16:33.425
-Is that you, Ed?!
-That's enough! Stop!

00:16:45.037 --> 00:16:47.006
Françoise!

00:16:52.444 --> 00:16:55.314
How's that? And that, and that?

00:17:03.722 --> 00:17:05.457
This is father-person.

00:17:06.325 --> 00:17:07.693
Father?

00:17:08.560 --> 00:17:09.661
Your father?

00:17:11.563 --> 00:17:13.432
She had such a thing?

00:17:14.133 --> 00:17:16.602
This is Spike-person and Jet-person.

00:17:16.668 --> 00:17:17.636
I see.

00:17:21.774 --> 00:17:24.176
No, father. Good people.

00:17:24.243 --> 00:17:25.611
Oh? I see.

00:17:26.445 --> 00:17:28.180
Thank you for taking care of my son.

00:17:29.148 --> 00:17:30.649
Or was it daughter?

00:17:31.383 --> 00:17:33.185
Oh ,well. It's all right either way.

00:17:34.286 --> 00:17:35.754
That's a token of my appreciation.

00:17:36.288 --> 00:17:40.225
Then, Ed, were you the one
who put the bounty on...?

00:17:41.326 --> 00:17:46.198
Fifty point zero, zero, zero,
zero, zero, zero?

00:17:47.332 --> 00:17:49.268
Only 50 woolongs?

00:17:49.601 --> 00:17:52.237
So, you wanna come with me?

00:18:02.748 --> 00:18:04.783
Hurry, Michael-duck!

00:18:05.317 --> 00:18:06.452
That's McIntire!

00:18:06.652 --> 00:18:07.653
Hey, wait!

00:18:09.721 --> 00:18:10.656
Father!

00:18:21.333 --> 00:18:22.568
He's gone.

00:20:27.392 --> 00:20:29.361
Hey, it's dinnertime.

00:20:39.538 --> 00:20:40.772
Spike, dinner.

00:21:26.051 --> 00:21:28.387
You can't come with me, Ein.

00:21:30.022 --> 00:21:32.958
Ed is going someplace far, far away.

00:21:33.625 --> 00:21:35.861
I might not be coming back.

00:21:37.529 --> 00:21:40.399
So, Ein, you should go back home.

00:21:44.670 --> 00:21:46.438
Do you want to come with Ed?

00:22:09.895 --> 00:22:11.096
Let's go, Ein!

00:22:41.993 --> 00:22:47.365
<i>Too much time has passed by</i>

00:22:47.566 --> 00:22:52.370
<i>To lament that we were deeply in love</i>

00:22:53.972 --> 00:22:58.810
<i>The wind keeps blowing, while my heart</i>

00:22:59.578 --> 00:23:04.416
<i>Cannot heal all the tears in it</i>

00:23:05.984 --> 00:23:12.991
<i>Someone cry for me with parched eyes.</i>

00:23:16.962 --> 00:23:20.098
<i>The real folk blues</i>

00:23:20.532 --> 00:23:23.034
<i>I only want to know</i>

00:23:24.703 --> 00:23:28.840
<i>What true sadness is</i>

00:23:28.907 --> 00:23:31.810
<i>Sitting in muddy water</i>

00:23:32.511 --> 00:23:35.147
<i>Isn't such a bad life</i>

00:23:36.681 --> 00:23:43.455
<i>If it ends</i>

00:23:46.491 --> 00:23:49.494
<i>After the first time</i>

00:24:06.011 --> 00:24:09.748
<i>Everything has a beginning and an end.</i>

00:24:10.182 --> 00:24:11.817
<i>Life is just a cycle of them.</i>

00:24:12.150 --> 00:24:17.088
<i>With unwanted endings, becoming an adult</i>

00:24:17.522 --> 00:24:20.458
<i>is to experience the inevitable finale.</i>

00:24:20.992 --> 00:24:23.862
<i>It's been a fast trip for Bebop,</i>
<i>with only two episodes left.</i>

00:24:24.496 --> 00:24:27.165
<i>But make sure you pay close attention</i>
<i>to how it ends.</i>

00:24:27.532 --> 00:24:30.669
<i>Next episode:</i>
<i>"The Real Folk Blues Part 1."</i>

